
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `eps2eps` yek file EPS (Encapsulated PostScript) ra migirad va aan ra be yek file EPS-e digar tabdil mikonad. In kar baraye behtar kardan sazegari (compatibility) ya taghir daadane andaze safhe anjam mishavad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `-o <file>`  --> 📤  Esme file khorooji ra moshakhas mikonad. Agar in gozine nabaashad, file asli jaigozin mishavad.
    🔹 `-sPAPERSIZE=<size>`  --> 📄  Andazeye kaaghaz ra baraye file jadid moshakhas mikonad (masalan, `letter`, `a4`).
    🔹 `-dCompressPages=true|false` --> 🗜️  File EPS ra compress mikonad ya na.  `true` baraye compress kardan va `false` baraye compress nakardan.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ eps2eps input.eps output.eps

    🔹 File `input.eps` ra be `output.eps` tabdil mikonad.

    $ eps2eps -sPAPERSIZE=a4 input.eps output.eps

    🔹 File `input.eps` ra be `output.eps` tabdil mikonad va andazeye aan ra be A4 taghir midahad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ eps2eps -o output.eps input.eps

    🔹 File `input.eps` ra be `output.eps` tabdil mikonad. Agar file `output.eps` ghablan voojood dashte bashad, jaigozin mishavad.  Agar `-o` estefade nashavad, `input.eps` jaigozin mishavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `eps2eps` command converts an EPS (Encapsulated PostScript) file to another EPS file. This is often done to improve compatibility or change the page size.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `-o <file>`  --> 📤 Specifies the output file name.  If this option is omitted, the original file is overwritten.
    🔹 `-sPAPERSIZE=<size>`  --> 📄 Specifies the paper size for the new file (e.g., `letter`, `a4`).
    🔹 `-dCompressPages=true|false` --> 🗜️  Compresses the EPS file or not. `true` to compress, and `false` to not compress.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ eps2eps input.eps output.eps

    🔹 Converts the file `input.eps` to `output.eps`.

    $ eps2eps -sPAPERSIZE=a4 input.eps output.eps

    🔹 Converts the file `input.eps` to `output.eps` and changes its page size to A4.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ eps2eps -o output.eps input.eps

    🔹 Converts `input.eps` to `output.eps`. If `output.eps` already exists, it will be overwritten.  If `-o` isn't used, `input.eps` itself is overwritten.
